      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start for the students to get the gist of it. I'm a bit worried though, some of the parents in our district might argue that this interpretation is just \"judicial activism\" and that the court is making up rights that aren't actually in the text. How should I address that criticism in the lesson? Should I frame it as a valid legal debate or just explain why the substantive due process approach is the standard way we protect liberty now?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
